{"title":"Bike check: Remco Evenepoel’s world champion Specialized Tarmac SL7","link":"https://www.cyclingtips.com/2023/05/bike-check-remco-evenepoels-world-champion-specialized-tarmac-sl7/","date":1683820250000,"content":"<figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Remco-Evenepoel-world-champion-specialized-tarmac-bike-ZW-Photography-Giro-dItalia-2023-Stage-2-06040.jpg?width=1200\" alt=\"Bike check: Remco Evenepoel's world champion Specialized Tarmac SL7\" /></figure><p>At 23 years old, <a href=\"http://cyclingtips.com/tag/Remco-Evenepoel\" target=\"_blank\">Remco Evenepoel</a> has already racked up an enviable <em>palmarès</em>, complete with two Liège-Bastogne-Liège victories and a grand tour GC win at last year’s Vuelta, only to be followed up with taking the rainbow jersey at the road world championships.</p>\n<p>This month, he’s attempting to add a Giro d’Italia grand tour GC victory to that list, and he’s off to a good start after winning the opening time trial to take the <em>maglia rosa</em> leader’s jersey. He has since ceded it but maintains an advantage over the top GC contenders in what could be a memorable grand tour.</p>\n<p>We got a closer look at Evenepoel’s <a href=\"http://cyclingtips.com/tag/specialized\" target=\"_blank\">Specialized</a> Tarmac SL7, which in addition to a special livery commemorating his world championship win, was also sporting pink handlebar tape to match his leader’s jersey for stage 2. The bike features a Shimano Dura-Ace groupset, Roval wheels, a Pro cockpit, and a Specialized saddle.</p>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Remco-Evenepoel-world-champion-specialized-tarmac-bike-ZW-Photography-Giro-dItalia-2023-Stage-2-06040.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"Remco Evenepoel's World Champion Edition Specialized Tarmac SL7 \" width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Remco-Evenepoel-world-champion-specialized-tarmac-bike-ZW-Photography-Giro-dItalia-2023-Stage-2-06040.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Remco-Evenepoel-world-champion-specialized-tarmac-bike-ZW-Photography-Giro-dItalia-2023-Stage-2-06040.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption>Remco Evenepoel’s world champion Specialized S-Works Tarmac SL7 features a Shimano Dura-Ace groupset, Roval wheels, a Pro cockpit, and a Specialized 3D-printed Mirror saddle. <span>(Photo: Zac Williams)</span></figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Remco-Evenepoel-world-champion-specialized-tarmac-bike-ZW-Photography-Giro-dItalia-2023-Stage-2-06058.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"Remco Evenepoel's World Champion Edition Specialized Tarmac SL7 close up\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Remco-Evenepoel-world-champion-specialized-tarmac-bike-ZW-Photography-Giro-dItalia-2023-Stage-2-06058.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Remco-Evenepoel-world-champion-specialized-tarmac-bike-ZW-Photography-Giro-dItalia-2023-Stage-2-06058.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption>Specialized has worked the world champion’s rainbow stripes into Evenepoel’s Tarmac. Tacx provides the team with bottle cages. <span>(Photo: Zac Williams)</span></figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Remco-Evenepoel-world-champion-specialized-tarmac-bike-ZW-Photography-Giro-dItalia-2023-Stage-2-06155.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Remco-Evenepoel-world-champion-specialized-tarmac-bike-ZW-Photography-Giro-dItalia-2023-Stage-2-06155.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Remco-Evenepoel-world-champion-specialized-tarmac-bike-ZW-Photography-Giro-dItalia-2023-Stage-2-06155.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption>Evenepoel even gets a rainbow-striped computer mount. Pro supplies Soudal Quick-Step with Vibe carbon handlebars. <span>(Photo: Zac Williams)</span></figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Remco-Evenepoel-world-champion-specialized-tarmac-bike-ZW-Photography-Giro-dItalia-2023-Stage-2-06121.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"Remco Evenepoel's World Champion Edition Specialized Tarmac SL7 toptube inscription\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Remco-Evenepoel-world-champion-specialized-tarmac-bike-ZW-Photography-Giro-dItalia-2023-Stage-2-06121.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Remco-Evenepoel-world-champion-specialized-tarmac-bike-ZW-Photography-Giro-dItalia-2023-Stage-2-06121.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption>The top tube commemorates Evenepoel’s world championship victory. <span>(Photo: Zac Williams)</span></figcaption></figure></figure>\n<p><strong>Also read: <a href=\"https://www.cyclingtips.com/2023/05/bike-check-mark-cavendishs-wilier-filante-slr-for-the-giro-ditalia/\" target=\"_blank\">Bike check: Mark Cavendish’s Wilier Filante SLR for the Giro d’Italia</a></strong></p>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Remco-Evenepoel-world-champion-specialized-tarmac-bike-ZW-Photography-Giro-dItalia-2023-Stage-2-06127.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"Remco Evenepoel's World Champion Edition Specialized Tarmac SL7 handlebar view\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Remco-Evenepoel-world-champion-specialized-tarmac-bike-ZW-Photography-Giro-dItalia-2023-Stage-2-06127.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Remco-Evenepoel-world-champion-specialized-tarmac-bike-ZW-Photography-Giro-dItalia-2023-Stage-2-06127.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption>Evenepoel likes his brake hoods toed in.</figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Remco-Evenepoel-world-champion-specialized-tarmac-bike-ZW-Photography-Giro-dItalia-2023-Stage-2-06112.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"Remco Evenepoel's World Champion Edition Specialized Tarmac SL7\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Remco-Evenepoel-world-champion-specialized-tarmac-bike-ZW-Photography-Giro-dItalia-2023-Stage-2-06112.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Remco-Evenepoel-world-champion-specialized-tarmac-bike-ZW-Photography-Giro-dItalia-2023-Stage-2-06112.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption>Soudal-Quick-Step uses the Tarmac SL7 on both climbing and flat stages due to its low weight and aero profile. (Photo: Zac Williams)</figcaption></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Remco-Evenepoel-world-champion-specialized-tarmac-bike-ZW-Photography-Giro-dItalia-2023-Stage-2-06051.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Remco-Evenepoel-world-champion-specialized-tarmac-bike-ZW-Photography-Giro-dItalia-2023-Stage-2-06051.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Remco-Evenepoel-world-champion-specialized-tarmac-bike-ZW-Photography-Giro-dItalia-2023-Stage-2-06051.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption>Evenepoel raced stage 2 on Roval Rapide CLX II wheels. <span>(Photo: Zac Williams)</span></figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Remco-Evenepoel-world-champion-specialized-tarmac-bike-ZW-Photography-Giro-dItalia-2023-Stage-2-06094.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"Remco Evenepoel's World Champion Edition Specialized Tarmac SL7 back angle\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Remco-Evenepoel-world-champion-specialized-tarmac-bike-ZW-Photography-Giro-dItalia-2023-Stage-2-06094.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Remco-Evenepoel-world-champion-specialized-tarmac-bike-ZW-Photography-Giro-dItalia-2023-Stage-2-06094.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption>The number 1 slot goes to Remco Evenepoel at this year’s Giro. Can he finish in that position? (Photo: Zac Williams)</figcaption></figure></figure>","author":"Will Tracy","siteTitle":"CyclingTips","siteHash":"30feca30fb3902119bf2da6559e7337232527b61c9abe0a00f5d7543c6aa6c84","entryHash":"b5db1c3bd16b97b1393c787bea47deb2465007c203e9cd6f1fba50e86b527758","category":"Cycling"}